values.c2bibtfvsd9d1rv: Located within the centre of the Skibotn Fjord, this is a brownfield site with exisiting industrial buildings, surrounded by natural woodland.
values.c5bs8q4bdki0hfd: A technical consultant such as Ramboll can be instructed to prepare and submit the building permits. Including technical design this is forecast to cost circa 60k EUR. The strategy would be to submit short form building permits which can be prepared, submitted and approved in 2-4 months.
values.cvody7eixj5r4zh:
The site is adjacent to the E8 highway that connects northern Finland to Norway, located ~6km from the town of Skitbotn. 

Exisiting brownfield infrastructure sees this site having suitable access at two points from the main road. However the same access road is used for a holiday park, so additional roads/ security measures would need to be taken to ensure site security. 

Current brownfield infrastructure is sufficient for drainage concerns.

values.coioy7zcbkhw9ro:
Once a short-form building permit is approved, an application can be made to Fingrid including ramp up plans and connection details. This would then be instantly approved and capacity allocated for a new 400kV line. 

The existing line 110kV line would not require a connection application.
values.c17ui7dv5as0i92: DISP inplace (with full political support). Zoning will take about 1 year from when the process starts. Zoning needs to be complete before new election (2027)
values.c0itd8mr2f455a1:

values.c78s362pz0myd9d:
A 7 MW power draw is possible to be implemented in the regional grid without addiitonal measures.

A new transformer will be installed to accommodate the remaining power draw above 7MW.

This assumes a number of investments in the distribution network, such as the establishment of a new feeder from the existing Skibotn substation  dedicated to our consumption. 

A suitable customer interface will be established at our connection point. 

The network infrastructure we develop within the distribution grid will be considered a customer-specific installation.
values.ck9emimxfbke0ew:
Needs a new main transformer at the local substation. New transformer/gas-insulated switchgear/component timeline is likely 2 years and timeline for concession is likely to be approximately 1 year.

Therefore expecting a 3 year timeline but seeking to shorten this through discussions with NVE who give approvals for the concessions to speed up the concession process.

Also connecting the DSO with suppliers we know who can supply transformers more quickly. Where those suppliers are not acceptable to the DSO we will engage domestic electrical engineering firms about recertifying and warranting transformers from alternative suppliers to the DSO.
